author: The Columbus Dispatch
title: High-school football | City League roundup: Centennial pulls away on kick return
text:
Centennial 40, Linden 27 

Tyler Patterson returned a kickoff 80 yards for a touchdown midway through the fourth quarter, and Centennial (3-6, 1-4) held off visiting Linden (1-8, 1-4) in the City League North. 

Centennial led 34-6 in the third quarter behind three TD passes from Dimitri Warner. But Linden rallied behind TD runs from Cordell Calloway and Da’Sean Henry. Rob Dalton’s 25-yard TD run midway through the fourth pulled Linden to within seven before Patterson scored on the ensuing kickoff. 

Patterson finished with 154 yards rushing and Warner had 141 yards rushing. Henry had 121 passing yards for Linden. 

Beechcroft 41, Whetstone 12 
Macyah Fleming, Rodell Rahmaan and Kyle Barrett each accounted for two touchdowns and Beechcroft (6-2, 5-0) defeated host Whetstone (4-5, 3-2) in the City North. Fleming ran for a score and threw a 61-yard TD pass to Rahmaan, who also had a punt return for a touchdown. Barrett threw a touchdown pass and ran for a score. Whetstone’s Jack Staggs had 231 yards passing and Aidan Tuttle had 10 receptions for 82 yards. 

Eastmoor Academy 26, West 6 
Terry Johnson sparked Eastmoor Academy (6-3, 5-1) with two second-quarter touchdowns and the Warriors defeated host West (4-5, 2-4) in the City South. Johnson returned a fumble 65 yards for a score and caught a 45-yard TD pass to give Eastmoor a 12-0 halftime lead. Daylin Jackson led Eastmoor with 134 yards rushing and the Warriors forced five turnovers, including three interceptions. 

Briggs 56, Africentric 18 
Tyson Miles completed 13 of 18 passes for 256 yards and four touchdowns, and Briggs (4-5, 2-4) scored 35 points in the second quarter to defeat host Africentric (2-7, 0-6) in the City South. AJ Houchins rushed for 209 yards and two TDs for Briggs. Tyler Potts completed 15 of 27 passes for 241 yards and Kaylin Perkins caught four passes for 120 yards for Africentric. 

Walnut Ridge 48, South 12 
Malik Harrison passed for three touchdowns and rushed for two scores for Walnut Ridge (6-3, 5-1) which beat host South (1-8, 1-5) in the City South. Harrison, who rushed for 65 yards and passed for 122 yards, threw two TD passes to Tarik Wright. Mar’ya Taylor caught a TD pass and ran for a score for Walnut Ridge. Devjuawan Robinson rushed for 170 yards and passed for 104 for South.
